<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-64-1139 </DOCNO><TEXT>The authors consider molecule formation by a two-step process: free-boundabsorption followed by reemission to a stable bound state or to a continuum.Calculations are carried out on the Na system by applying the theoryof laser-induced collisions proposed by Julienne and Mies to an ensembleof laser-cooled Na atoms at 10/sup -3/ K. The process can take placewithin either the singlet or triplet manifold of molecular states.</TEXT></DOC>